-- Lazard Hires Noah Bulkin in London From Bank of America
-- B y   A m b e r e e n   C h o u d h u r y
-- 2012-01-09T09:32:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/lazard-hires-noah-bulkin-in-london-from-bank-of-america-1-.html
Lazard Ltd. (LAZ) , the largest non-bank
merger adviser, hired Noah Bulkin from  Bank of America (BAC)  Corp. as
a managing director advising U.K. companies on acquisitions.  Bulkin, who will be based in London, was a managing
director in the Europe, Middle East and Africa advisory team at
Bank of America, Lazard said in a Business Wire statement today.  He has “advised on many landmark transactions in the U.K.
particularly in the energy, consumer, real estate and leisure
sectors,” said William Rucker, chief executive officer of
Lazard in London, in the statement.  Lazard reported a 24 percent increase in revenue to $199.1
million from mergers and acquisitions in the third quarter. It
ranked ninth on the M&A league tables in 2011, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
